article:
The following is a 'list of [[7400 series]] digital logic [[integrated
circuit]]s'. The SN7400 series originated with TTL integrated circuits made by
Texas Instruments. Because of the popularity of these parts, they were second-
sourced by other manufacturers who kept the 7400 sequence number as an aid to
identification of compatible parts. As well, compatible TTL parts originated by
other manufacturers were second sourced in the TI product line under a 74xxx
series part number.

Just the base numbers are listed below, that is: parts are listed here as if
made in the basic, standard power and speed, TTL form, although many later parts
were never manufactured with that technology. __TOC__ {|class="wikitable"
